{
    "attributes": {
        "action": "Give self employed people Tax Breaks equivalent to 5.6 weeks Holiday entitlement",
        "additional_details": "We feel it\u2019s very unfair to be self employed when it comes to holidays. We get no paid time off. We think self-employed workers should get a tax break to the equivalent monetary value of 5.6 weeks annual leave.",
        "background": "Almost all workers are legally entitled to 5.6 weeks paid holiday per year, self employed people get 0 and may lose a weeks wage for going on a weeks holiday. ",
